  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6768 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6765 (-16.9B) and max positive at 6780 (+11.7B), dealers are currently in heavy buying mode as they hedge short gamma positions in this breakout regime. The massive negative gamma concentration from 6760-6770 creates a volatility amplification zone where dealer hedging will accelerate any directional moves, while the positive gamma wall at 6780 acts as the immediate resistance where dealers flip to selling pressure. Watch for explosive moves if we break below 6765 (dealers buy more aggressively) or above 6780 (dealer selling kicks in), with the gex_surge event confirming heightened hedging activity is already underway.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent swings between 6765-6780 with breakouts likely to trend hard.",
